category%20in%20the%20federal%20budget.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20systems%20and%20programs%20may%20be%20more%20resistant%20to%20change%20than%20others.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20tapped%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ceo-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20spearhead%20cuts%20to%20government%20spending%2C%20and%20the%20defense%20sector%20could%20be%20a%20prime%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Defense%20Department's%20budget%20for%20the%202024%20fiscal%20year%20is%20%24841%20billion%2C%20roughly%2012.5%25%20of%20the%20total%20federal%20budget%2C%20and%20the%20Pentagon%20has%20struggled%20with%20cost%20overruns%20and%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20plans%20to%20review%20federal%20spending%20as%20part%20of%20a%20newly%20created%20%26quot%3BDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-elon-musk-vivek-ramaswamy-department-government-efficiency-doge-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDOGE%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20not%20an%20official%20agency%2C%20and%20Congress%20controls%20budgets%20for%20federal%20agencies.%20DOGE's%20role%20may%20be%20limited%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-vivek-ramaswamy-doge-government-efficiency-what-us-spends-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffering%20advice%20to%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20still%20a%20lot%20of%20unknowns%20around%20DOGE%20as%20it%20solicits%20direction%20from%20X%2C%20formerly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20where%20and%20how%20it'll%20find%20up%20to%20%242%20trillion%20in%20promised%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Musk's%20past%20comments%20hint%20at%20one%20area%20he%20could%20target%3A%20defense%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20criticized%20government%20contracts%20with%20top%20defense%20companies%20that%20put%20the%20government%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20overages%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20warships%2C%20aircraft%2C%20and%20combat%20vehicles.%20And%20his%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20won%20some%20government%20contracts%20by%20bearing%20higher%20risks%20of%20cost%20overruns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283ac3479-807f-4415-a020-96d80c7f3594%5C%22%3EMusk's%20way%20of%20doing%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Musk%20founded%20SpaceX%20in%202001%2C%20NASA%20and%20the%20Pentagon%20often%20used%20%26quot%3Bcost-plus%26quot%3B%20contracts%2C%20which%20reimbursed%20contractors%20for%20their%20expenses%20and%20provided%20a%20set%20profit%20margin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223541%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20listens%20as%20Elon%20Musk%20speaks%20during%20a%20campaign%20rally%20in%20Pennsylvania%20last%20month.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673789f8fa0140cdd563c9ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20listens%20as%20Elon%20Musk%20speaks%20during%20a%20campaign%20rally%20in%20Pennsylvania%20in%20October.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJulia%20Demaree%20Nikhinson%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20contracts%20allowed%20for%20cost%20overruns%20and%20placed%20much%20of%20the%20risk%20on%20the%20US%20government%2C%20Clayton%20Swope%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20think%20tank%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20compared%20the%20contracts%20to%20%26quot%3Bgravy%20trains%26quot%3B%20in%20journalist%20Walter%20Isaacson's%20biography%20of%20the%20billionaire.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20can't%20get%20to%20Mars%20with%20that%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20an%20incentive%20never%20to%20finish.%20If%20you%20never%20finish%20a%20cost-plus%20contract%2C%20then%20you%20suckle%20on%20the%20tit%20of%20the%20government%20forever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20built%20SpaceX's%20business%20model%20around%20fixed-price%20contracts.%20This%20means%20the%20government%20and%20contractors%20set%20a%20price%20for%20the%20project%20at%20the%20onset%2C%20and%20the%20company%20is%20paid%20predetermined%20amounts%20once%20it%20hits%20certain%20milestones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20has%20had%20several%20fixed-price%20contracts%20with%20NASA%2C%20including%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fnews-release%2Ffirst-contracted-spacex-resupply-mission-launches-with-nasa-cargo-to-space-station%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241.6%20billion%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202008%20for%2012%20missions%20under%20the%20agency's%20Commercial%20Resupply%20Services%20program%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2Fspacex_nasa_crs-5_presskit-105.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242.6%20billion%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202014%20that%20covered%20six%20crewed%20missions%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20previously%20reserved%20fixed-price%20contracts%20for%20off-the-shelf%20products%20that%20did%20not%20need%20to%20be%20specially%20made%20for%20the%20government%2C%20but%20SpaceX%20demonstrated%20that%20it%20could%20fund%20missions%20more%20efficiently%2C%20Swope%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20processes%20and%20tracking%20required%20for%20cost-plus%20contracts%2C%20companies%20like%20SpaceX%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20more%20agile%20to%20changes%20in%20the%20market%20and%20iterate%20on%20their%20products%20faster%2C%26quot%3B%20Swope%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it's%20done%20right%2C%20it%20can%20be%20beneficial%20to%20both%20the%20government%20and%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224453%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20SpaceX%20Falcon%20Heavy%20rocket%20with%20a%20NASA%20spacecraft%20bound%20for%20Jupiter%20lifts%20off%20from%20pad%2039A%20at%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20in%20October.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67378a35192f52589858e278%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222969%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20SpaceX%20Falcon%20Heavy%20rocket%20with%20a%20NASA%20spacecraft%20bound%20for%20Jupiter%20lifts%20off%20from%20pad%2039A%20at%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20in%20October.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJohn%20Raoux%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3b24f6e-1253-4bfb-9623-5ba146b04d68%5C%22%3EOverspending%20and%20delays%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20has%20often%20been%20criticized%20for%20mismanagement%2C%20delays%2C%20and%20ballooning%20costs%20on%20expensive%20systems.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20a%20government%20watchdog%20found%20that%20the%20F-35%20stealth%20fighter%20program%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-f-35-stealth-fighters-to-fly-less-costs-soar-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20more%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20expected%20lifetime%20costs%20topping%20%242%20trillion%2C%C2%A0even%20with%20the%20aircraft%20flying%20less%20often%20than%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20industry%2C%20like%20the%20military%2C%20has%20also%20been%20called%20to%20account.%20Major%20shipbuilding%20projects%2C%20for%20example%2C%20are%20severely%20delayed.%20Coming%20off%20problems%20with%20the%20Zumwalt-class%20destroyers%2C%20first-in-class%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%2C%20and%20the%20Littoral%20Combat%20Ship%2C%20new%20constructions%20like%20the%20next%20Ford-class%20carrier%2C%20Constellation-class%20frigate%2C%20and%20Columbia-class%20submarine%20are%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-grappling-with-another-ford-class-supercarrier-delay-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyears%20behind%20schedule%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20a%20concern%20as%20the%20US%20military%20aims%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-not-ready-china-war-military-economy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaintain%20its%20edge%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20its%20%26quot%3Bpacing%20challenge%26quot%3B%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20DoD%20has%20faced%20criticism%20over%20use-it-or-lose-it%20spending%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20the%20fiscal%20year%2C%20overpayment%20for%20common%20products%2C%20and%20seven%20consecutive%20failed%20audits%20of%20the%20department's%20%244.1%20trillion%20in%20assets%20and%20%244.3%20trillion%20in%20liabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20tackle%20the%20contracting%20conundrum%20and%20save%20money%2C%20Mike%20Gallagher%2C%20a%20former%20Republican%20congressman%20from%20Wisconsin%20and%20the%20current%20head%20of%20defense%20at%20Palantir%20Technologies%2C%20suggested%20in%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fopinion%2Ftwo-years-to-prevent-world-war-iii-trump-sec-def-needs-to-overhaul-bureaucracy-cut-waste-c9a162d8%3Fmod%3Dopinion_lead_pos5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eop-ed%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week%20that%20the%20incoming%20Pentagon%20leadership%20should%20enforce%20fixed-price%20contracting%20to%20put%20more%20burden%20on%20private%20contractors%20rather%20than%20the%20US%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Defense%20Department's%20cost-plus%20contracting%20model%20has%20destroyed%20competition%20and%20innovation%20while%20exploding%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20Gallagher%20wrote%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20defense%20secretary%20should%20be%20required%20to%20sign%20off%20on%20cost-plus%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20new%20initiative%20could%20recommend%20exactly%20this%3A%20a%20move%20away%20from%20cost-plus%20contracts%20toward%20fixed-price%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223841%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20at%20Newport%20News%20Shipbuilding%20in%20Virginia%20in%20April%202016.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67378b2bfa0140cdd563ca48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222475%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20at%20Newport%20News%20Shipbuilding%20in%20Virginia%20in%20April%202016.%3Cp%3ESteve%20Helber%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20fixed-price%20contracting%20may%20have%20its%20own%20set%20of%20problems.%20Bryan%20McGrath%2C%20a%20retired%20naval%20officer%20and%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20The%20FerryBridge%20Group%20LLC%2C%20responded%20to%20Gallagher's%20article%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fconswahoo%2Fstatus%2F1857138300307624153%3Fs%3D46%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20social%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20private%20companies%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20face%20all%20the%20costs%20for%20systems%20that%20only%20the%20US%20government%20wants%20to%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETodd%20Harrison%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%20who%20focuses%20on%20defense%20strategy%20and%20budgeting%2C%20said%20switching%20from%20cost-plus%20to%20fixed-price%20contracting%20doesn't%20necessarily%20save%20the%20government%20money.%20It%20also%20doesn't%20necessarily%20produce%20more%20effective%20systems%20designed%20to%20withstand%20combat%20or%20decades%20of%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20it%20does%20is%2C%20by%20moving%20the%20risk%20to%20industry%2C%20it%20creates%20more%20stability%20for%20government%20and%20what%20they're%20going%20to%20pay%20for%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20puts%20better%20incentives%20on%20industry%2C%20because%20if%20industry%20has%20a%20cost%20overrun%2C%20they%20pay%20for%20it%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20coming%20out%20of%20their%20profit.%20If%20they%20can%20deliver%20below%20cost%20that%20they%20expected%2C%20they%20can%20make%20more%20money.%20So%20it%20really%20just%20changes%20the%20incentives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarrison%20said%20that%20there%20had%20already%20been%20a%20shift%20toward%20firm-fixed-price%20contracts%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20advantage%20smaller%20and%20newer%20defense%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20a%20trend%20he%20expects%20will%20accelerate%20during%20the%20Trump%20administration.%20But%20there%20are%20some%20areas%20where%20cost-plus%20contracts%20are%20sure%20to%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShipbuilding%2C%20especially%20for%20projects%20like%20aircraft%20carriers%20and%20nuclear-powered%20submarines%2C%20is%20often%20arranged%20with%20large%2C%20multi-year%20contracts.%20This%20is%20because%20there%20may%20be%20only%20one%20company%20that%20can%20build%20the%20system%2C%20with%20one%20buyer%20(the%20Pentagon)%2C%20and%20the%20product%20is%20unique%20to%20the%20US%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221876%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20digital%20rendering%20of%20the%20Constellation-class%20frigate.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67378b87fa0140cdd563ca63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22869%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20digital%20rendering%20of%20the%20Constellation-class%20frigate.%3Cp%3EBAE%20Systems%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20those%20areas%20of%20the%20defense-industrial%20base%2C%26quot%3B%20Harrison%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20have%20to%20manage%20it%20more%20like%20a%20public%20utility%2C%20where%20the%20free%20market%20does%20not%20exist%2C%20and%20free%20market%20principles%20do%20not%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22719bae83-1982-40bc-bd4e-defb6b11920c%5C%22%3EMore%20efficient%20programs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMid-development%20changes%20to%20weapons%20systems%20designs%20are%20a%20major%20cost%20driver.%20To%20tackle%20this%2C%20the%20government%20could%20fix%20requirements%20for%20these%20systems%20early%20in%20the%20design%20process%20and%20enforce%20stricter%20rules%20around%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20way%20that%20we%20know%20saves%20money%20is%20if%20you%20fix%20a%20design%20and%20don't%20add%20features%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Bohnert%2C%20a%20licensed%20engineer%20at%20the%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday's%20F-35%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Balmost%20a%20different%20plane%26quot%3B%20than%20what%20was%20defined%20in%20its%20original%20requirements.%20Changes%20in%20scope%20have%20added%20costs.%20%26quot%3BYou%20look%20at%20other%20programs%20that%20have%20been%20pretty%20narrowly%20defined%20%E2%80%94%20they've%20stayed%20in%20budget%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArcher%20Macy%2C%20a%20retired%20Navy%20admiral%20and%20missile%20defense%20expert%20at%20CSIS%2C%20told%20BI%20there's%20a%20history%20of%20abusing%20contracts%20where%20there's%20too%20much%20fluidity%20with%20requirements%20and%20specifications%2C%20making%20them%20vulnerable%20to%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20government%20needs%20to%20find%20the%20%26quot%3Bright%20type%20of%20contract%20for%20the%20right%20purpose%20(where%20you%20are%20in%20the%20development%20and%20acquisition%20cycle)%2C%20stick%20to%20and%20don't%20abuse%20requirements%20and%20specs%2C%20and%20make%20people%20accountable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225396%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20view%20of%20the%20Pentagon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647d228c40bf000019fa2813%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223598%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20aerial%20view%20of%20the%20Pentagon%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FPatrick%20Semansky%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20new%20initiative%20may%20target%