0few%20key%20distinctions%20that%20could%20spell%20big%20differences%20in%20how%20each%20company%20is%20affected%20by%20rising%20import%20costs.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Wong%2FJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20America's%20grocery%20king%2C%20Walmart%20sources%20a%20high%20share%20of%20its%20products%20from%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETarget%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20relies%20more%20on%20merchandise%20that%20is%20often%20imported%2C%20such%20as%20apparel%20and%20housewares.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20difference%20puts%20more%20of%20Target's%20business%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20impacted%20if%20Trump%20follows%20through%20on%20his%20tariff%20promises.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-and-target-are-looking-increasingly-similar-these-days-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilarities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Walmart%20and%20Target%20have%20key%20distinctions%20that%20could%20spell%20big%20differences%20in%20how%20each%20would%20be%20affected%20by%20rising%20import%20costs%20if%20Donald%20Trump%20follows%20through%20with%20his%20promised%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTarget%20is%20actually%20much%20more%20exposed%20than%20Walmart%20because%20Walmart%20is%20grocery-heavy%20and%20groceries%20are%20predominantly%20domestic%2C%26quot%3B%20Jason%20Miller%2C%20supply%20chain%20professor%20at%20Michigan%20State%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-grocery-sales-us-compared-kroger-albertsons-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20grocery%20king%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Walmart%20US%20makes%20nearly%2060%25%20of%20its%20revenue%20from%20the%20grocery%20category%20and%20only%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20sales%20from%20general%20merchandise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20grocery%20as%20a%20share%20of%20sales%20has%20been%20increasing%20in%20recent%20years%20as%20the%20general%20merchandise%20share%20has%20declined%2C%20according%20to%20Walmart's%20annual%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarget%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20relies%20much%20more%20heavily%20on%20merchandise%20that%20is%20often%20imported%2C%20such%20as%20apparel%2C%20housewares%2C%20and%20beauty.%20Food%20and%20beverage%20sales%20accounted%20for%20less%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20Target's%20sales%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETD%20Cowen%20retail%20analyst%20Oliver%20Chen%20told%20BI%20that%20Target's%20apparel%20segment%20presents%20another%20potential%20complication%2C%20as%20fashion%20is%20more%20sensitive%20to%20seasonality.%20That%20could%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20to%20pull%20orders%20forward%20ahead%20of%20possible%20tariffs%20or%20line%20up%20new%20suppliers%20in%20time%20to%20still%20be%20in%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20miss%20apparel%20timeline%2C%20you%20don't%20get%20it%20back%2C%20and%20Target%20has%20more%20apparel%20exposure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20its%20grocery-to-merchandise%20ratio%2C%20Walmart%20has%20another%20key%20advantage%20over%20Target%3A%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWalmart%20is%20much%20bigger%2C%26quot%3B%20Kantar%20analyst%20Gina%20Logan%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I'm%20not%20just%20talking%20about%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20a%20much%20more%20advanced%20supply%20chain%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20a%20wider%20range%20of%20suppliers%2C%20they%20have%20more%20ability%20to%20pivot%20and%20predict%20demand%2C%20and%20can%20use%20their%20automation%20and%20forecasting%20in%20order%20to%20react%20to%20this%20in%20a%20much%20faster%2C%20more%20predictive%20way%20than%20Target.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20the%20Spark%20has%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-finding-groove-should-terrify-target-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20competitive%20advantage%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20Bullseye%20in%20the%20grocery%20aisle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20US%20shoppers%20began%20to%20cut%20spending%20back%20in%202023%2C%20prioritizing%20essentials%20like%20groceries%20in%20their%20weekly%20budgets%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-sales-boom-target-slides-as-shoppers-shift-to-groceries-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esales%20at%20Walmart%20chugged%20along%20while%20Target%20struggled%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarget%20has%20since%20found%20success%20by%20taking%20a%20much%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-lowers-prices-battles-walmart-customers-shopping-for-deals-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWalmart-like%20stance%20with%20price%20cuts%20and%20bargain%20brands%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20its%20share%20of%20grocery%20sales%20has%20increased%20by%201-2%20percentage%20points%20per%20year%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELogan%20says%20tariffs%2C%20if%20announced%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20would%20likely%20push%20Target%20harder%20into%20the%20grocery%20game%2C%20especially%20with%20its%20portfolio%20of%20private-label%20food%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarget%20and%20Walmart%20both%20report%20earnings%20next%20week.%20Walmart%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story%2C%20citing%20the%20quiet%20period%2C%20and%20Target%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20BI's%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20time%20the%20companies'%20executives%20discussed%20tariffs%20on%20earnings%20calls%20was%20in%202019%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20AlphaSense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Walmart%20said%20it%20would%20not%20raise%20prices%20on%20food%20impacted%20by%20tariffs%20and%20would%20instead%20look%20to%20offset%20the%20cost%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20guest-focused%20retailer%2C%26quot%3B%20Target%20CEO%20Brian%20Cornell%20said%20in%20May%202019%2C%20%