getown%20University%20and%20the%20Roosevelt%20Institute%2C%20a%20left-leaning%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirms%2C%20including%20AutoZone%20and%20Columbia%20Sportswear%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-trump-tariffs-inflation-goods-getting-more-expensive-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20already%20indicated%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0they%20will%20raise%20prices%20if%20tariffs%20are%20enacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20shoppers%20and%20small%20businesses%20told%20BI%20they%20are%20also%20preparing.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40antiplasticlady%2Fvideo%2F7435678703147076910%3Famp%253Bt%3D1731358479116%26q%3Dtariffs%2520under%2520trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20videos%3C%2Fa%3E%20recommending%20viewers%20stock%20up%20on%20certain%20goods%20like%20hair%2C%20makeup%2C%20and%20clothing%20products%20are%20racking%20up%20thousands%20of%20views%2C%20and%20panicked%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaroline%20Leavitt%2C%20a%20Trump-Vance%20transition%20spokeswoman%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3BTrump%20instituted%20tariffs%20against%20China%20that%20created%20jobs%2C%20spurred%20investment%2C%20and%20resulted%20in%20no%20inflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsidering%20the%20larger%20scale%20of%20Trump's%20proposals%20this%20time%20around%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etrade%20experts%20have%20identified%20goods%2C%20including%20car%20parts%2C%20apparel%2C%20and%20electronics%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-trump-tariffs-will-impact-prices-technology-clothes-appliances-furniture-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproducts%20at%20risk%20of%20getting%20more%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20Trump's%20tariff%20proposals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20big%20shift%20if%20that%20does%20come%20to%20fruition%2C%26quot%3B%20Hull%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20pay%20tariffs%20on%20some%20things%20anyway%2C%20but%20the%20talk%20of%20the%20massive%20increase%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20alarming%20to%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2255855a54-34f3-4348-894e-b4b4454ea037%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdopting%20%26quot%3Bprepper%26quot%3B%20methods%20and%20stocking%20up%20on%20groceries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%2042-year-old%20mother%20of%20three%20in%20Southern%20Indiana%2C%20whose%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20BI%20but%20withheld%20over%20privacy%20concerns%2C%20is%20leaning%20back%20into%20her%20prepper%20roots.%20Before%20the%20pandemic%20and%20Trump's%20second%20run%2C%20she%20tried%20to%20forget%20the%20%26quot%3Bcraziness%26quot%3B%20of%20her%20old-school%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-doomsday-preppers-why-are-they-right-wing-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoomsday%20prepper%3C%2Fa%3E%20background.%20She%20was%20raised%20by%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20original%20conspiracy%20theorist%20guys%20who%20had%20serious%20distrust%20of%20the%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she's%20leaned%20back%20into%20it.%20She%20estimates%20that%20her%20family%20has%20spent%20upwards%20of%20%242%2C800%20to%20%243%2C000%20slowly%20preparing%20and%20stockpiling%20goods%2C%20including%20everything%20from%20buying%20meats%20from%20a%20local%20butcher%20and%20deep-freezing%20them%20to%20dehydrating%20food%20for%20a%20longer%20shelf%20life.%20She%20got%20started%20early%3A%20As%20soon%20as%20she%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bgut%20feeling%26quot%3B%20Trump%20was%20running%20again%2C%20her%20family%20began%20their%20slow%20stockpile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20aren't%20like%20the%20ones%20you%20used%20to%20see%20on%20Discovery%20Channel%20with%20bunkers%20and%20huge%20stashes%20of%20stuff%2C%20but%20we%20have%20enough%20to%20get%20through%203-5%20years%20at%20least%20of%20hard%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDutta-Gupta%20said%20it's%20reasonable%20for%20families%20to%20want%20to%20stock%20up%20on%20imported%20goods%2C%20as%20trade%20wars%20and%20tax%20changes%20could%20reduce%20incomes%20and%20raise%20the%20cost%20of%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarissa%20Garcia%2C%2038%2C%20said%20she%20didn't%20pay%20much%20attention%20to%20tariffs%20prior%20to%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Trump's%20victory%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20started%20making%20a%20list%20of%20the%20potential%20items%20that%20could%20be%20affected%2C%20and%20then%20narrowing%20them%20down%20to%20the%20actual%20things%20that%20would%20affect%20my%20family%2C%20the%20things%20that%20I%20would%20be%20sad%20about%20if%20we%20couldn't%20afford%20next%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20week%20after%20the%20election%2C%20she%20%26quot%3Bwent%20to%20the%20store%20and%20made%20my%20first%20of%20hopefully%20many%20shopping%20trips%20to%20start%20stocking%20up%20on%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EItems%20on%20Garcia's%20list%20include%20frozen%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%2C%20garlic%2C%20coffee%2C%20tea%2C%20and%20bread%2C%20all%20of%20which%20would%20be%20subject%20to%20tariffs.%20She%20also%20said%20she's%20planning%20to%20stock%20up%20on%20hygiene%20supplies%20like%20sanitizer%20and%20masks.%20These%20purchases%20are%20costing%20around%20an%20additional%20%2450%20on%20her%20grocery%20trips%2C%20and%20although%20money%20is%20tight%20%E2%80%94%20she%20got%20laid%20off%20last%20year%20and%20is%20freelancing%20as%20she%20looks%20for%20a%20permanent%20role%20%E2%80%94%20she%20said%20she%20anticipates%20an%20even%20greater%20financial%20strain%20under%20Trump's%20proposed%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanprogressaction.org%2Farticle%2Ftrumps-tariff-would-cost-the-typical-american-household-roughly-1500-each-year%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20left-leaning%20Center%20for%20American%20Progress%20found%20that%20Trump's%20tariff%20plans%20would%20cost%20the%20average%20household%20an%20extra%20%241%2C500%20a%20year%2C%20and%20the%20nonpartisan%20Peterson%20Insitute%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.piie.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-09%2Fwp24-20.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Trump's%20proposed%2060%25%20tariff%20on%20Chinese%20goods%20would%20boost%20inflation%20by%200.4%20percentage%20points%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarcia%20said%20that%20learning%20of%20those%20estimates%20alarmed%20her.%20%26quot%3BMy%20family%20cannot%20afford%20that.%20This%20year%20was%20rough%20enough%2C%20and%20that%20was%20really%20surprising%20and%20also%20just%20a%20scary%20feeling%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d8a08791-1bb1-4d36-b97a-e72031c68494%5C%22%3ESmall%20business%20owners%20are%20trying%20to%20stock%20up%2C%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorries%20about%20potential%20tariffs%20are%20already%20taking%20a%20financial%20toll%20on%20Beatrice%20Barba%2C%2039%2C%20who%20owns%20a%20small%20business%20that%20produces%20plastic-free%20cups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarba%20said%20she%20imports%20most%20of%20the%20materials%20she%20needs%20to%20produce%20her%20cups%20from%20China.%20She's%20considering%20purchasing%20a%20year's%20worth%20of%20inventory%20now%2C%20which%20she%20estimates%20would%20cost%20up%20to%20%24200%2C000%20plus%20the%20price%20of%20additional%20warehouse%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20taking%20that%20risk%20is%20worth%20it%20because%20she%20wants%20to%20do%20everything%20she%20can%20to%20ensure%20she%20does%20not%20have%20to%20raise%20the%20price%20of%20her%20goods%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20longer-term%20solution%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe's%20working%20with%20a%20developer%20to%20build%20a%20health%20advice%20app%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20a%20business%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe%20plans%20to%20prioritize%20because%20an%20app%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewould%20not%20be%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esubject%20to%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELisa%20Evans%2C%20a%2043-year-old%20salon%20owner%20in%20Jacksonville%2C%20Florida%2C%20is%20examining%20where%20her%20products%20are%20sourced.%20Even%20hair%20color%20dyes%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emanufactured%20in%20the%20US%20might%20contain%20ingredients%20from%20abroad%2C%20and%20their%20prices%20could%20surge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20hair%20in%20already-costly%20extensions%20is%20sourced%20from%20China%2C%20and%20she%20worries%20how%20much%20more%20expensive%20that%20will%20get.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20she's%20focusing%20on%20padding%20inventory%20going%20into%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20hope%20for%20the%20best%2C%20but%20prepare%20for%20the%20worst%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Gold%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20supply%20chain%20and%20customs%20policy%20at%20the%20National%20Retail%20Federation%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20even%20though%20it's%20still%20unclear%20what%20exactly%20Trump%20will%20implement%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20bad%20idea%20for%20both%20companies%20and%20consumers%20to%20prepare%20for%20any%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20a%20very%20different%20economy%20now%20than%20when%20we%20were%20back%20in%202018%20when%20the%20initial%20China%20tariffs%20were%20put%20in%20place%2C%20and%20the%20scale%20and%20scope%20of%20what%20is%20being%20proposed%20is%20going%20to%20impact%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Gold%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20companies%20aren't%20able%20to%20absorb%20all%20of%20that%2C%20so%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20pass%20on%20some%20of%20those%20costs%20to%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJavon%20Ford%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20chemist%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20said%20that%20tariffs%20can%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Broadblock%26quot%3B%20to%20procuring%20raw%20materials.%20Ford%20is%20considering%20stocking%20up%20on%20color%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epigments%20for%