age%20of%20Nordic-inspired%20cabins%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20a%20five-acre%20parcel%20of%20land%20in%20Waco%20on%20Zillow%2C%20just%20a%20few%20miles%20from%20my%20home.%20In%20March%202021%2C%20I%20purchased%20the%20land%20using%20a%20short-term%20loan%20and%20personal%20savings%20for%20%24138%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20nine%20and%20a%20half%20months%2C%20I%20managed%20the%20design%20and%20construction%20of%20a%20seven-unit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarting-successful-tiny-house-airbnb-business-tips-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicro-resort%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20an%20immersive%20natural%20setting.%20I%20financed%20the%20build%20with%20a%20construction%20loan%20from%20a%20local%20community%20bank%20and%20through%20raising%20equity%20from%20friends%20and%20family.%20It%20cost%20%242.5%20million%20to%20build%2C%20including%20a%20container%20pool%20and%20hot%20tubs%2C%20which%20we%20added%20later%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20launched%20in%20January%202022.%20A%20travel%20influencer%20who%20marketed%20the%20resort%20on%20Instagram%20helped%20us%20go%20viral%20and%20generate%20a%20huge%20number%20of%20bookings.%20It%20was%20like%20an%20instant%20goldmine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20went%20all%20in%20on%20Instagram%2C%20growing%20the%20brand%20through%20creating%20content%20and%20partnering%20with%20influencers.%20Some%20of%20our%20early%20guests%20became%20superfans%2C%20coming%20back%20multiple%20times%20a%20year%20and%20bringing%20others%20with%20them.%20In%20our%20first%2012%20months%20of%20being%20open%2C%20we%20brought%20in%20%24860%2C000%20in%20bookings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20time%20we%20operated%20the%20business%2C%20I%20kept%20in%20mind%20that%20if%20someone%20came%20and%20offered%20the%20right%20price%20and%20terms%2C%20I%3Cem%3E'%3C%2Fem%3Ed%20consider%20selling%20it.%20I%20believe%20that%20every%20material%20possession%20should%20have%20a%20price%20tag%20attached%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sold%20the%20property%2C%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiny-house-airbnb-hotel-waco-texas-see-inside-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELive%20Oak%20Lake%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20%247%20million%20in%20October%202023.%20I%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20securing%20a%20deal%2C%20including%20the%20value%20of%20having%20a%20good%20broker%20and%20attorneys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2225fde6b5-f457-43bf-be94-6ce8e4254041%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20uniqueness%20of%20the%20property%20helped%20us%20get%20a%20good%20price%20on%20the%20sale%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELive%20Oak%20Lake%20was%20like%20my%20baby.%20I%20built%20it%20from%20the%20ground%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20three%20months%20after%20we%20opened%20were%20challenging.%20I%20was%20learning%20how%20to%20integrate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-passive-income-hospitality-short-term-rental-airbnb-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproperty%20management%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20my%20wife%20was%20doing%20the%20cleaning.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20hired%20a%20part-time%20cleaning%20and%20guest%20communications%20manager%20and%20a%20part-time%20operations%20manager%2C%20who%20then%20ran%20the%20property%20after%20the%20first%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20then%20spending%20around%20five%20to%2010%20hours%20a%20week%20on%20the%20business%2C%20mostly%20doing%20marketing.%20Because%20you're%20open%20for%20business%2024%2F7%20in%20hospitality%2C%20some%20of%20those%20hours%20were%20late%20at%20night%20when%20guests%20were%20arriving%20late.%20I%20was%20doing%20personal%20branding%20and%20coaching%20alongside%20the%20hotel.%20My%20wife%20and%20I%20also%20did%20mission%20work%20with%20our%20church.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20I%20considered%20selling%20Live%20Oak%20Lake%20was%20because%20of%20the%20stress%20of%20running%20it.%20Even%20though%20I%20automated%20elements%20for%20efficiency%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-jobs-restaurants-hotels-leisure-hospitality-healthcare-government-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehospitality%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20guest%20experience%20is%20paramount.%20I%20was%20focused%20on%20blowing%20guests%20away%20and%20wanted%20to%20look%20at%20every%20single%20review.%20It%20was%20hard%20to%20unplug%20from%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20listed%20Live%20Oak%20Lake%20for%20sale%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202022.%20Several%20parties%20were%20interested%2C%20but%20we%20felt%20the%20property%20was%20worth%20more.%20We%20removed%20that%20listing%20and%20raised%20the%20price%20by%20%241%20million%20when%20we%20next%20listed%20in%20January%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20broker%20who%20specialized%20in%20outdoor%20hospitality%20reached%20out%20and%20helped%20me%20from%20there.%20When%20we%20relisted%20the%20property%2C%20the%20broker%20helped%20vet%20the%20interested%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20about%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-sales-tips-for-closing-deals-faster-2016-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclose%20on%20a%20deal%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%246.5%20million%2C%20but%20the%20buyers%20backed%20out%20the%20day%20before%20we%20were%20set%20to%20close.%20It%20was%20an%20emotional%20roller%20coaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20days%20later%2C%20we%20received%20another%20offer%20for%20%247%20million%20from%20a%20private%20group%20of%20investors%2C%20which%20we%20were%20able%20to%20close%20on.%20The%20property%20is%20being%20run%20similarly%20to%20before%2C%20and%20some%20of%20my%20friends%20who%20I%20hired%20to%20manage%20things%20on%20the%20ground%20still%20work%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20uniqueness%20and%20novelty%20of%20the%20property%2C%20the%20audience%20we%20built%2C%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20hospitality%20we%20offered%20helped%20us%20sell%20for%20that%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20weren't%20in%20a%20hurry%20to%20sell%2C%20but%20%247%20million%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20Plus%2C%20I%20hit%20it%20off%20with%20the%20buyer%20and%20liked%20their%20vision.%20I%20felt%20they%20understood%20what%20made%20us%20special%2C%20like%20our%20social%20media%20following%2C%20direct%20bookings%2C%20and%20unique%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7a0c906-c322-4402-99d2-bf69962ff44c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20learned%20a%20valuable%20lesson%20about%20selling%20a%20property%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20learned%20from%20the%20selling%20process%20was%20the%20importance%20of%20having%20good%20attorneys%20and%20a%20great%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-to-find-real-estate-agent%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebroker%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20broker%20was%20local%2C%20which%20was%20a%20huge%20help.%20There%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhome-inspection%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproperty%20inspections%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20meetings%20with%20prospective%20buyers.%20He%20could%20help%20with%20those%20things%20without%20me%20having%20to%20drop%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20alleviated%20my%20emotional%20volatility%20and%20attachment%20to%20the%20property%20because%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20every%20interaction.%20I'm%20a%20very%20detail-oriented%20person%20who%20likes%20to%20micromanage%20things.%20I%20needed%20to%20trust%20other%20people%2C%20like%20my%20attorneys%20and%20the%20broker%2C%20who%20could%20take%20my%20hands%20off%20of%20the%20selling%20process.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20highly%20recommend%20getting%20a%20broker%20to%20anyone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuilders-new-construction-rental-homes-investors-price-cuts-mortgage-rates-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eselling%20a%20property%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f9154a67-a1d5-4e4c-a88c-c48ff6eebfa6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESelling%20the%20property%20has%20alleviated%20my%20stress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20I%20sold%20Live%20Oak%20Lake%20at%20the%20right%20time.%20I%20held%20the%20property%20just%20long%20enough%20to%20gain%20thorough%20experience%20operating%20a%20micro-resort%20and%20build%20it%20to%20a%20point%20where%20it%20was%20really%20valuable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESelling%20has%20alleviated%20stress%20in%20my%20life.%20I%20have%20an%20office%20and%20art%20studio%20in%20my%20backyard%2C%20where%20I%20can%20now%20work%20on%20other%20ventures%20as%20and%20when%20I%20want.%20I%20consult%20with%20other%20micro-resort%20developers%2C%20which%20is%20how%20I'm%20funding%20my%20lifestyle%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20I%20would%20own%20and%20operate%20another%20project%2C%20but%20I'd%20want%20to%20hire%20a%20full-time%20manager%20that%20I%20could%20train%20to%20manage%20our%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Live%20Oak%20Lake%20project%20was%20an%20amazing%20project%2C%20a%20baptism%20by%20fire%20in%20the%20realms%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftips-real-estate-investing-expert-get-started-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20hospitality.%20The%20price%20was%20right%2C%20so%20it%20made%20sense%20to%20sell%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20real%20estate%20story%20you%20want%20to%20share%20with%20Business%20Insider%3F%20Email%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsold-airbnb-property-selling-lessons-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publish