spond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20helped%20found%20OpenAI%20in%202015%20but%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-elon-musk-and-sam-altman-relationship-feuds-2023-3%23in-2023-it-was-reported-that-sam-altman-and-other-openai-cofounders-had-rejected-musks-proposal-to-run-the-company-in-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrequently%20criticized%20the%20company%20and%20its%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20years%20since.%20The%20SpaceX%20CEO%20left%20the%20AI%20startup%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20amended%20complaint%20filed%20in%20federal%20court%20this%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ceo-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk%3C%2Fa%3E%20outlined%20the%20beginnings%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20including%20the%20initial%20emails%20Altman%20sent%20him%20proposing%20the%20idea%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20Musk%20characterized%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAltman's%3C%2Fa%3E%20initial%20outreach%20to%20Musk%20as%20him%20%26quot%3Btesting%20the%20waters%26quot%3B%20and%20trying%20to%20convince%20the%20Tesla%20CEO%20to%20bring%20his%20funding%20and%20connections%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20March%202015%2C%20the%20two%20tech%20leaders%20drafted%20an%20open%20letter%20to%20the%20US%20government%20highlighting%20the%20need%20for%20regulation%20in%20the%20safe%20creation%20of%20AI%2C%20the%20complaint%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20sensed%20an%20%26quot%3Bopportunity%26quot%3B%20following%20the%20letter%2C%20Musk's%20lawyers%20allege%2C%20leading%20him%20to%20email%20Musk%20the%20following%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EBeen%20thinking%20a%20lot%20about%20whether%20it's%20possible%20to%20stop%20humanity%20from%20developing%20AI.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20think%20the%20answer%20is%20almost%20definitely%20not.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20it's%20going%20to%20happen%20anyway%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20it%20would%20be%20good%20for%20someone%20other%20than%20Google%20to%20do%20it%20first.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EAny%20thoughts%20on%20whether%20it%20would%20be%20good%20for%20YC%20to%20start%20a%20Manhattan%20Project%20for%20AI%3F%20My%20sense%20is%20we%20could%20get%20many%20of%20the%20top%20~50%20to%20work%20on%20it%2C%20and%20we%20could%20structure%20it%20so%20that%20the%20tech%20belongs%20to%20the%20world%20via%20some%20sort%20of%20nonprofit%20but%20the%20people%20working%20on%20it%20get%20startup-like%20compensation%20if%20it%20works.%20Obviously%20we'd%20comply%20with%2Faggressively%20support%20all%20regulation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ESam%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20responded%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EProbably%20worth%20a%20conversation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EA%20month%20later%2C%20Altman%20followed%20up%20on%20Musk's%20%26quot%3Bnoncommital%26quot%3B%20response%20and%20offered%20Musk%20a%20detailed%20proposal%20for%20a%20new%20AI%20lab%2C%20according%20to%20the%20court%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E1.)%20The%20mission%20would%20be%20to%20create%20the%20first%20general%20AI%20and%20use%20it%20for%20individual%20empowerment%E2%80%94ie%2C%20the%20distributed%20version%20of%20the%20future%20that%20seems%20the%20safest.%20More%20generally%2C%20safety%20should%20be%20a%20first-class%20requirement.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E2.%20)%20I%20think%20we'd%20ideally%20start%20with%20a%20group%20of%207-10%20people%2C%20and%20plan%20to%20expand%20from%20there.%20We%20have%20a%20nice%20extra%20building%20in%20Mountain%20View%20they%20can%20have.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E3.)%20I%20think%20for%20a%20governance%20structure%2C%20we%20should%20start%20with%205%20people%20and%20I'd%20propose%20you%2C%20Bill%20Gates%2C%20Pierre%20Omidyar%2C%20Dustin%20Moskovitz%2C%20and%20me.%20The%20technology%20would%20be%20owned%20by%20the%20foundation%20and%20used%20%26quot%3Bfor%20the%20good%20of%20the%20world%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20in%20cases%20where%20it's%20not%20obvious%20how%20that%20should%20be%20applied%20the%205%20of%20us%20would%20decide.%20The%20researchers%20would%20have%20significant%20financial%20upside%20but%20it%20would%20be%20uncorrelated%20to%20what%20they%20build%2C%20which%20should%20eliminate%20some%20of%20the%20conflict%20(we'll%20pay%20them%20a%20competitive%20salary%20and%20give%20them%20YC%20equity%20for%20the%20upside).%20We'd%20have%20an%20ongoing%20conversation%20about%20what%20work%20should%20be%20open-sourced%20and%20what%20shouldn't.%20At%20some%20point%20we'd%20get%20someone%20to%20run%20the%20team%2C%20but%20he%2Fshe%20probably%20shouldn't%20be%20on%20the%20governance%20board.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E4.)%20Will%20you%20be%20involved%20somehow%20in%20addition%20to%20just%20governance%3F%20I%20think%20that%20would%20be%20really%20helpful%20for%20getting%20work%20pointed%20in%20the%20right%20direction%20getting%20the%20best%20people%20to%20be%20part%20of%20it.%20Ideally%20you'd%20come%20by%20and%20talk%20to%20them%20about%20progress%20once%20a%20month%20or%20whatever.%20We%20generically%20call%20people%20involved%20in%20some%20limited%20way%20in%20YC%20%26quot%3Bpart-time%20partners%26quot%3B%20(we%20do%20that%20with%20Peter%20Thiel%20for%20example%2C%20though%20at%20this%20point%20he's%20very%20involved)%20but%20we%20could%20call%20it%20whatever%20you%20want.%20Even%20if%20you%20can't%20really%20spend%20time%20on%20it%20but%20can%20be%20publicly%20supportive%2C%20that%20would%20still%20probably%20be%20really%20helpful%20for%20recruiting.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E5.)%20I%20think%20the%20right%20plan%20with%20the%20regulation%20letter%20is%20to%20wait%20for%20this%20to%20get%20going%20and%20then%20I%20can%20just%20release%20it%20with%20a%20message%20like%20%26quot%3Bnow%20that%20we%20are%20doing%20this%2C%20I've%20been%20thinking%20a%20lot%20about%20what%20sort%20of%20constraints%20the%20world%20needs%20for%20safefy.%26quot%3B%20I'm%20happy%20to%20leave%20you%20off%20as%20a%20signatory.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ESam%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20responded%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EAgree%20on%20all%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20thus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20was%20born.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20stepped%20down%20from%20OpenAI's%20board%20of%20directors%20in%202018.%20Years%20later%2C%20Semafor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.semafor.com%2Farticle%2F03%2F24%2F2023%2Fthe-secret-history-of-elon-musk-sam-altman-and-openai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Musk%20wanted%20to%20run%20the%20company%20on%20his%20own%20to%20beat%20Google.%20When%20his%20request%20was%20rejected%2C%20Musk%20pulled%20his%20funding%20and%20left%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20first%20sued%20OpenAI%20and%20its%20cofounders%20in%20March%2C%20alleging%20the%20company%20had%20shirked%20its%20nonprofit%20mission%20by%20partnering%20with%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20has%20invested%20more%20than%20%2413%20billion%20in%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-elon-musk-ai-lawsuit-sam-altman-harassing-legal-battle-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time%20called%20the%20suit%20%26quot%3Bincoherent%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bcontradictory.%26quot%3B%20Musk%20dro