mpetitive%20capability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20Wall%20Street%2C%20whose%20hype%20over%20generative%20AI%20catapulted%20Microsoft%20to%20a%20%243%20trillion%20valuation%2C%20has%20begun%20to%20sour%20on%20the%20huge%20AI%20swings%20that%20some%20companies%20have%20begun%20to%20take.%20In%20June%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20published%20a%20report%2C%20%26quot%3BGen%20AI%3A%20Too%20Much%20Spend%2C%20Too%20Little%20Benefit%3F%26quot%3B%20that%20speculated%20an%20industry-wide%20bubble%20could%20soon%20burst.%20Venture%20capitalists%20have%20also%20tempered%20their%20enthusiasm.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20Marc%20Andreessen%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20AI-bullish%20venture%20firms%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hiring-boom-marc-andreessen-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndreessen%20Horowitz%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20warned%20that%20AI%20models%20were%20hitting%20a%20%26quot%3Bceiling%20on%20capabilities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225040%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Satya%20Nadella%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6737638d192f52589858d0c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223542%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BCopilot%20will%20fundamentally%20transform%20our%20relationship%20with%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20said%20when%20he%20debuted%20the%20AI%20assistant%20last%20year.%3Cp%3EEthan%20Miller%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20estimates%20that%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20tech%20companies%20will%20invest%20more%20than%20%241%20trillion%20to%20develop%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Microsoft%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20spenders.%20Thanks%20in%20large%20part%20to%20its%20AI%20strategy%2C%20the%20company's%20capital%20expenditures%20hit%20a%20record%20%2420%20billion%20in%20its%20most%20recent%20quarter%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20company's%20expenses%20said%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20Microsoft's%20history%20that%20capital%20expenses%20have%20started%20to%20exceed%20its%20payroll%2C%20which%20now%20encompasses%20228%2C000%20employees.%20Internally%2C%20BI%20has%20learned%2C%20the%20spending%20spree%20on%20AI%20delayed%20budgets%20for%20several%20teams%20for%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year.%20It%20has%20also%20prompted%20the%20company%20to%20add%20Copilot-specific%20sales%20goals%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eturning%20up%20the%20pressure%20to%20wring%20revenue%20out%20of%20its%20massive%20investment%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20technology%20is%20still%20in%20its%20formative%20stages%2C%20and%20Microsoft's%20big%20bet%20may%20eventually%20pay%20off%2C%20given%20enough%20time%20and%20resources.%20But%20as%20the%20company%20seeks%20to%20win%20over%20more%20converts%20to%20its%20gospel%20of%20generative%20AI%2C%20some%20of%20its%20own%20preachers%20wonder%20whether%20the%20company%20is%20worshiping%20a%20false%20god.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20gap%20between%20the%20ambitious%20vision%20and%20what%20users%20are%20actually%20experiencing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20another%20employee%20close%20to%20Copilot.%20%26quot%3BInternally%2C%20we're%20calling%20it%20growing%20pains.%20We%20are%20building%20the%20plane%20as%20we%20fly%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20November%2C%20when%20Microsoft%20released%20Copilot%20into%20its%20enterprise%20software%20suite%2C%20Microsoft%20365%2C%20it%20called%20the%20AI%20assistant%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20powerful%20productivity%20tool%20on%20the%20planet.%26quot%3B%20Copilot%20was%20able%20to%20almost%20instantaneously%20summarize%20meetings%20and%20emails.%20It%20seemed%20like%20the%20wave%20of%20the%20future%2C%20and%20it%20quickly%20took%20off%3A%20Microsoft%20says%2070%25%20of%20Fortune%20500%20companies%20now%20use%20Copilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInternally%2C%20though%2C%20some%20employees%20feared%20the%20company%20was%20releasing%20the%20product%20prematurely%20%E2%80%94%20a%20move%20that%20could%20backfire%20with%20customers.%20One%20employee%20who%20works%20with%20Copilot%20said%20that%20its%20PowerPoint%20tool%20was%20initially%20%26quot%3Bterrible%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20even%20now%20many%20of%20its%20features%20for%20Excel%20won't%20work%20without%20assistance%20from%20third-party%20vendors.%20A%20C-level%20executive%20at%20a%20large%20Microsoft%20customer%20told%20BI%20that%20many%20of%20Copilot's%20tools%20struck%20him%20as%20%26quot%3Bgimmicky.%26quot%3B%20By%20March%2C%20according%20to%20current%20and%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-copilot-future-openai-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexecutives%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20was%20engaging%20in%20a%20mad%20dash%20to%20add%20value%20to%20the%20product%2C%20before%20the%20initial%20excitement%20wore%20off.%20One%20Microsoft%20executive%20offered%20a%20blunt%20assessment%20of%20Copilot's%20ability%20to%20deliver%20useful%20results.%20%26quot%3BAbout%20one%20out%20of%2010%20times%20is%20magic%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20executive%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20rest%20of%20the%20time%20it's%3A%20Why%20do%20we%20even%20try%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20defends%20its%20new%20product%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20larger%20strategy%20of%20going%20all%20in%20on%20AI.%20The%20company%20told%20BI%20that%20its%20investments%20in%20Copilot%20are%20already%20paying%20off%2C%20and%20that%20many%20customers%20are%20coming%20back%20to%20purchase%20additional%20access%20to%20the%20tool.%20Microsoft%20also%20cited%20a%20study%20it%20commissioned%2C%20which%20found%20that%20for%20every%20%241%20a%20company%20devoted%20to%20generative%20AI%2C%20the%20return%20on%20investment%20was%20%243.70.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJared%20Spataro%2C%20Microsoft's%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20of%20AI%20at%20Work%2C%20dismissed%20criticism%20from%20the%20likes%20of%20Benioff%20as%20a%20rival's%20sour%20grapes.%20%26quot%3BHistory%20tells%20us%20that%20when%20competitors%20talk%20about%20you%2C%20it's%20because%20they're%20behind%2C%26quot%3B%20Spataro%20told%20BI.%20He%20also%20cited%20what%20he%20said%20were%20examples%20of%20Copilot's%20success%3A%20Lumen%20Technologies%20projects%20that%20its%20sales%20team's%20use%20of%20Copilot%20will%20save%20the%20company%20%2450%20million%20a%20year.%20Honeywell%20has%20used%20Copilot%20to%20add%20productivity%20gains%20equal%20to%20187%20full-time%20employees.%20And%20the%20fintech%20giant%20Finastra%20has%20cut%20creative%20production%20to%20seven%20weeks%20from%20seven%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20year%20after%20Copilot's%20release%2C%20such%20examples%20may%20be%20more%20outliers%20than%20the%20norm.%20In%20the%20Gartner%20survey%20published%20last%20month%2C%20IT%20leaders%20were%20far%20from%20enthusiastic%20about%20the%20product.%20Ninety-two%20percent%20said%20Copilot%20enhanced%20employee%20satisfaction%2C%20and%2062%25%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20valuable.%26quot%3B%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20nearly%2075%25%20said%20their%20employees%20were%20struggling%20to%20integrate%20Copilot%20into%20their%20daily%20routines%2C%2057%25%20said%20users%20felt%20the%20tool%20didn't%20deliver%20the%20value%20they%20expected%2C%20and%2053%25%20reported%20that%20it%20provided%20too%20many%20inaccurate%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDYh18%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22What%20IT%20leaders%20say%20about%20Microsoft%20365%20Copilot%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22484%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20also%20complain%20that%20Copilot%20%E2%80%94%20which%20at%20%2430%20a%20month%20per%20user%20can%20effectively%20double%20the%20licensing%20fee%20for%20Microsoft%20365%20%E2%80%94%20is%20far%20too%20costly.%20In%20July%2C%20Wall%20Street%20analysts%20noted%20that%20the%20chief%20information%20officer%20of%20a%20pharmaceuticals%20company%20had%20canceled%20Copilot%20for%20500%20employees%20after%20six%20months%2C%20saying%20the%20tool%20cost%20too%20much%20for%20what%20it%20provided.%20Some%20features%20didn't%20work%20well%2C%20the%20CIO%20said%2C%20likening%20the%20quality%20of%20its%20slide-generating%20capability%20to%20that%20of%20%26quot%3Bmiddle%20school%20presentations.%26quot%3B%20Even%20worse%2C%20what%20had%20initially%20struck%20him%20as%20Copilot's%20most%20compelling%20feature%20%E2%80%94%20its%20meeting-summary%20tool%20%E2%80%94%20had%20to%20be%20disabled%20because%20the%20company's%20legal%20team%20was%20wary%20of%20saving%20transcripts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20biggest%20concern%20customers%20have%20raised%20about%20Copilot%20involves%20its%20security.%20The%20tool's%20magic%20%E2%80%94%20its%20ability%20to%20create%20a%2010-slide%20road-mapping%20presentation%2C%20or%20to%20summon%20up%20a%20list%20of%20your%20company's%20most%20profitable%20products%20last%20quarter%20%E2%80%94%20works%20by%20browsing%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eindexing%20all%20of%20your%20company's%20internal%20information%2C%20like%20the%20web%20crawlers%20used%20by%20search%20engines.%20Historically%2C%20IT%20departments%20at%20many%20companies%20have%20set%20up%20lax%20permissions%20for%20who%20can%20access%20internal%20documents%20%E2%80%94%20selecting%20%26quot%3Ballow%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20say%2C%20for%20the%20company's%20HR%20software%2C%20rather%20than%20going%20through%20the%20trouble%20of%20selecting%20specific%20users.%20That%20never%20created%20much%20of%20a%20problem%2C%20because%20there%20wasn't%20a%20tool%20that%20an%20average%20employee%20could%20use%20to%20identify%20and%20retrieve%20sensitive%20company%20documents.%20But%20Copilot%20is%20that%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20many%20customers%20have%20deployed%20Copilot%2C%20only%20to%20discover%20that%20it%20can%20enable%20employees%20to%20read%20an%20executive's%20inbox%20or%20access%20sensitive%20HR%20documents.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20when%20Joe%20Blow%20logs%20into%20an%20account%20and%20kicks%20off%20Copilot%2C%20they%20can%20see%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20Microsoft%20employee%20familiar%20with%20customer%20complaints.%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20a%20sudden%20Joe%20Blow%20can%20see%20the%20CEO's%20emails.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20Microsoft%20employee%20said%20the%20tool%20%26quot%3Bworks%20really%20darn%20well%26quot%3B%20at%20sharing%20%26quot%3Binformation%20that%20the%20customer%20doesn't%20want%20to%20share%20or%20didn't%20think%20it%20had%20made%20available%20to%20its%20employee%2C%20such%20as%20salary%20info.%26quot%3B%20And%20fixing%20the%20issue%20is%20far%20from%20simple%2C%20said%20the%20previous%20employee%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20that%20it%20takes%20years.%20These%20are%20not%20easy%20situations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFaced%20with%20such%20issues%2C%20some%20customers%20have%20paused%20their%20deployment%20of%20Copilot.%20In%20the%20Gartner%20survey%2C%2040%25%20percent%20of%20IT%20managers%20said%20their%20company%20had%20delayed%20implementing%20the%20tool%20for%20at%20least%20three%20months%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Boversharing%20and%20security%20concerns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20has%20addressed%20Copilot's%20security%20issues%20in%20several%20ways.%20It%20has%20developed%20features%20to%20help%20customers%20manage%20their%20permissions%20at%20scale%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20identify%20where%20oversharing%20might%20be%20taking%20place.%20It%20has%20created%20a%20tool%20that%20enables%20users%20to%20keep%20files%20in%20libraries%20that%20are%20blocked%20from%20appearing%20in%20Copilot-generated%20results.%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EAnd%20later%20this%20month%2C%20it%20plans%20to%20release%20a%20guide%20%26quot%3Bthat%20specifically%20addresses%20the%20topic%20of%20oversharing%2C%20with%20best%20practices%20to%20help%20customers%20manage%20their%20data%20securely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20company%20insiders%2C%20Copilot%20has%20also%20been%20hampered%20by%20a%20program%20Microsoft%20introduced%20this%20year%20called%20the%20Secure%20Future%20Initiative.%20The%20move%20%E2%80%94%20which%20makes%20security%20the%20top%20priority%20for%20every%20employee%20%E2%80%94%20follows%20years%20of%20security%20issues%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20including%20what%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20cascade%20of%20security%20failures%26quot%3B%20last%20year%20that%20allowed%20Chinese%20hackers%20to%20access%20emails%20from%20thousands%20of%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20faced%20with%20the%20tradeoff%20between%20security%20and%20another%20priority%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Microsoft%20employees%20in%20the%20spring%2C%20%26quot%3Byour%20answer%20is%20clear%3A%20Do%20security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInternally%2C%20employees%20have%20been%20impressed%20by%20the%20initiative.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20biggest%20company%20push%20I've%20ever%20seen%20Microsoft%20do%20where%20they%20are%20investing%20in%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one.%20But%20some%20also%20say%20that%20the%20emphasis%20on%20security%20is%20delaying%20the%20development%20of%20new%20Copilot%20features%2C%20which%20are%20desperately%20needed%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20more%20customers.%20%26quot%3BSecurity%20continues%20to%20be%20job%20No.%201%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20employee%20familiar%20with%20the%20initiative%2C%20%26quot%3Beven%20if%20it's%20deferring%20feature%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20blog%20post%20in%20September%2C%20Microsoft%20said%20it%20was%20continuing%20to%20add%20capabilities%20to%20address%20customer%20concerns.%20%26quot%3BNearly%201%2C000%20customers%20have%20given%20us%20feedback%20on%20how%20they're%20using%20Copilot%2C%20where%20it%20is%20having%20the%20biggest%20impact%2C%20and%20where%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20post%20said.%20%26quot%3BBased%20on%20that%20feedback%2C%20we%20have%20made%20more%20than%20700%20product%20updates%20and%20shipped%20over%20150%20new%20features%20this%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20updates%20do%20happen%2C%20employees%20say%2C%20they%20sometimes%20make%20things%20worse.%20A%20recent%20attempt%20to%20update%20to%20the%20consumer%20version%20of%20Copilot%20sparked%20complaints%20among%20employees%20on%20an%20internal%20message%20board%20viewed%20by%20BI.%20Users%20said%20the%20new%20version%20was%20%26quot%3Bdumber%26quot%3B%20than%20the%20previous%20version%2C%20providing%20less%20real-time%20information%20and%20often%20answering%20queries%20with%2C%20%26quot%3BSorry%2C%20I%20can't%20help%20you%20with%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20getting%20better%2C%20some%20people%20feel%20it%20lost%20functionality%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20also%20expressed%20frustration%20at%20what%20they%20see%20as%20the%20company's%20tendency%20to%20slap%20the%20Copilot%20brand%20on%20everything%20in%20sight.%20In%20the%20past%20year%2C%20Microsoft%20has%20released%20Copilot%20into%20office%20apps%2C%20the%20Windows%20operating%20system%2C%20the%20Edge%20browser%2C%20and%20several%20other%20products.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20delusion%20on%20our%20marketing%20side%20where%20literally%20everything%20has%20been%20renamed%20to%20have%20Copilot%20it%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20employee.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20is%20Copilot.%20Nothing%20else%20matters.%20They%20want%20a%20Copilot%20tie-in%20for%20everything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20wants%20to%20make%20their%20impact%20by%20jamming%20a%20bad%20Copilot%20chatbot%20into%20their%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20another%20longtime%20employee.%20%26quot%3BSo%20now%20every%20time%20I%20click%20on%20certain%20links%2C%20I%20get%20two%20pop-ups%20for%20crappy%20Copilot%20implementations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20complaints%20and%20questions%20over%20Copilot%20mount%2C%20both%20inside%20and%20outside%20Microsoft%2C%20so%20does%20the%20pressure%20to%20justify%20the%20company's%20unprecedented%20level%20of%20spending%20on%20AI.%20According%20to%20an%20internal%20document%20from%20April%2C%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20to%20serve%20its%20skyrocketing%20needs%20for%20data%20storage%20and%20processing%2C%20the%20company%20plans%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-gpu-targets-1-8-million-ai-chips-this-year-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eamass%201.8%20million%20chips%20known%20as%20GPUs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20each%20of%20which%20costs%20about%20%2430%2C000.%20By%20July%202025%2C%20it%20plans%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-plan-double-triple-data-center-capacity-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etriple%20its%20data-center%20capacity%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20already%20at%205%20gigawatts%2C%20roughly%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20power%20all%20of%20New%20York%20City%20each%20day.%20And%20by%202027%2C%20the%20company%20plans%20to%20spend%20more%20than%20%24100%20billion%20on%20GPUs%20and%20data%20centers%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20exercise%20in%20mass%20delusion%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Gary%20Marcus%2C%20a%20well-known%20tech%20critic%20who%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BTaming%20Silicon%20Valley%3A%20How%20We%20Can%20Ensure%20that%20AI%20Works%20for%20Us.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20people%20invested%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecouple%20hundred%20billion%20dollars%20on%20basically%20hope%20and%20hype%20is%20embarrassing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarcus%20believes%20the%20tech%20industry%20is%20headed%20toward%20an%20%26quot%3BAI%20winter%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20Microsoft%20and%20other%20tech%20giants%20will%20pay%20a%20steep%20price%20for%20their%20extravagant%20investment%20in%20the%20technology%20without%20solving%20the%20fundamental%20problems%2C%20like%20hallucinations%2C%20that%20continue%20to%20plague%20AI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20Wile%20E.%20Coyote%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20cliff%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20people%20are%20going%20to%20realize%20they%20are%20over%20the%20end%20of%20the%20cliff%20and%20panic.%20Valuations%20are%20going%20to%20drop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Salesforce%20CEO%20Marc%20Benioff.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671b75449b3250dbbcea0a23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20has%20%26quot%3Bnot%20delivered%20any%20competitive%20capability%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Salesforce%20CEO%20Marc%20Benioff%2C%20who%20has%20released%20a%20rival%20product%20called%20Agentforce.%3Cp%3EBront%C3%AB%20Wittpenn%2FSan%20Francisco%20Chronicle%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20employees%20with%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20company's%20strategy%2C%20Microsoft%20intends%20to%20make%20its%20massive%20bet%20on%20AI%20pay%20off%20in%20two%20primary%20ways%3A%20by%20boosting%20sales%20and%20by%20repackaging%20prices.%20For%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year%2C%20which%20began%20in%20July%2C%20Microsoft%20has%20changed%20its%20sales%20goals%20to%20prioritize%20selling%20AI%20tools.%20And%20over%20the%20summer%2C%20the%20company%20considered%20a%20sweeping%20plan%20to%20repackage%20AI%20features%20into%20existing%20licenses%20or%20to%20create%20a%20more%20expensive%20bundle%20with%20Copilot%20AI%20capabilities.%20But%20those%20efforts%20stalled%20in%20September%20amid%20concerns%20about%20whether%20the%20plan%20would%20actually%20succeed.%20Instead%2C%20Judson%20Althoff%2C%20Microsoft's%20chief%20commercial%20officer%2C%20opted%20for%20a%20pilot%20program%20to%20test%20more%20expensive%20bundles%2C%20and%20then%20roll%20out%20significant%20licensing%20changes%20next%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20free%20up%20more%20capital%20for%20AI%2C%20the%20company%20has%20made%20significant%20cuts%20%E2%80%94%20including%20to%20its%20main%20businesses.%20Last%20year%20Microsoft%20slashed%20hundreds%20of%20jobs%20from%20Azure%2C%20the%20world's%20second%20most%20popular%20cloud%20computing%20platform.%20In%20an%20internal%20email%20explaining%20the%20decision%20to%20employees%2C%20Jason%20Zander%2C%20the%20executive%20vice%20president%20of%20Azure%2C%20said%20the%20cuts%20were%20made%20specifically%20to%20support%20the%20AI%20push.%20%26quot%3BOur%20clear%20focus%20as%20a%20company%20is%20to%20define%20the%20AI%20wave%20and%20empower%20all%20our%20customers%20to%20succeed%20in%20the%20adoption%20of%20this%20transformative%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20Zander%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20on%20the%20Azure%20team%20questioned%20the%20wisdom%20of%20cutting%20back%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20given%20the%20revenue%20it%20provides%20and%20the%20services%20it's%20responsible%20for.%20%26quot%3BThe%20AI%20team%20gets%20all%20the%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20the%20Azure%20team%20that%20is%20not%20only%20paying%20the%20bills%20but%20we%20are%20the%20ones%20doing%20all%20of%20the%20heavy%20lifting%20with%20security%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%20Another%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BAI%20is%20great%20and%20it%20might%20be%20the%20future%2C%20but%20when%20are%20you%20going%20to%20focus%20on%20your%20billpayers%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FzWPK6Enr-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Microsoft%20is%20betting%20big%20on%20AI.%20Company%20insiders%20have%20serious%20doubts.%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20has%20also%20cut%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20working%20on%20its%20Teams%20chat%20app%2C%20according%20to%20an%20internal%20memo%20shared%20with%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIn%20early%202022%2C%20we%20recognized%20the%20pandemic%20as%20a%20once-in-a-generation%20opportunity%20and%20we%20surged%20on%20Teams%20to%20win%2C%26quot%3B%20Spataro%20explained%20in%20the%20email.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20we're%20doing%20it%20again%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20but%20this%20time%2C%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJob%20cuts%20aren't%20the%20only%20way%20Microsoft%20is%20funding%20its%20AI%20push.%20To%20attract%20top%20talent%2C%20the%20company%20is%20paying%20significantly%20more%20for%20AI%20employees%20than%20for%20other%20roles.%20As%20of%20September%2C%20according%20to%20a%20payroll%20spreadsheet%20shared%20with%20BI%2C%20average%20compensation%20in%20the%20Microsoft%20AI%20group%20was%20about%2037%25%20higher%20than%20the%20average%20for%20all%20of%20the%20company's%20US%20employees.%20Software%20engineers%20within%20Microsoft%20AI%2C%20for%20example%2C%20earned%2048%25%20more%20than%20the%20average%20software-engineering%20role%20at%20the%20company.%20The%20message%20is%20clear%3A%20If%20you're%20applying%20to%20Microsoft%2C%20it%20pays%20to%20find%20a%20role%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20single-minded%20focus%20on%20AI%20has%20left%20many%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20including%20top%20leaders%2C%20feeling%20both%20frustrated%20and%20alarmed.%20%26quot%3BAI%20could%20be%20disruptive.%20We've%20got%20to%20be%20first.%20I%20get%20all%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20executive%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20a%20company%20of%20our%20size%20should%20be%20able%20to%20do%20multiple%20things%20at%20once.%20It%20seems%20like%20we%20can%20only%20think%20of%20one%20shiny%20object%20at%20a%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20a%20year%20after%20his%20sweeping%20claims%20that%20Copilot%20would%20uplift%20all%20of%20humanity%2C%20Nadella%20delivered%20a%20far%20more%20modest%20keynote%20address%20unveiling%20%26quot%3Bwave%20two%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20technology.%20To%20some%20within%20the%20company%2C%20the%20presentation%20appeared%20to%20signal%20a%20marked%20shift%20in%20the%20way%20Microsoft%20was%20casting%20Copilot%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20as%20if%20it%20were%20an%20admission%20that%20things%20weren't%20going%20to%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20Nadella%20used%20to%20boast%20about%20the%20company's%20partnership%20with%20OpenAI%20%E2%80%94%20whose%20large%20language%20model%20is%20what%20drives%20Copilot's%20responsiveness%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20instead%20referring%20to%20LLMs%20simply%20as%20%26quot%3Bcommodities.%26quot%3B%20And%20instead%20of%20touting%20Copilot%20as%20the%20best%2C%20most%20magical%20tool%20of%20its%20kind%2C%20he%20said%20the%20product%20would%20now%20be%20branded%20in%20more%20technical%20language%2C%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BUI%20for%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223749%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jared%20Spataro%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6733fad15ec9bfa3d63db505%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225623%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJared%20Spataro%2C%20Microsoft's%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20of%20AI%20at%20Work%2C%20says%20the%20company%20is%20exhibiting%20%26quot%3Bstrategic%20patience%26quot%3B%20over%20its%20massive%20investment%20in%20AI.%3Cp%3ETasos%20Katopodis%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20The%20Atlantic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSatya%20is%20resetting%2C%20after%20a%20good%20several%20years%20of%20saying%20the%20opposite%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20executive%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20trying%20to%20reinvent%20themselves.%20The%20narrative%20has%20shifted%20away%20from%20them.%20Right%20now%2C%20it's%20a%20lot%20of%2C%20'If%20you%20build%20it%2C%20they%20will%20come%2C'%20which%20hasn't%20happened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompetitors%20also%20scoffed%20at%20the%20presentation%20as%20show%20over%20substance.%20%26quot%3BMicrosoft's%20trying%20to%20rebrand%2C%26quot%3B%20Benioff%20told%20BI%20%E2%80%94%20a%20pivot%2C%20he%20said%2C%20necessitated%20by%20what%20he%20called%20Copilot's%20lack%20of%20%26quot%3BAI%20solutions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20notes%20that%20the%20number%20of%20Fortune%20500%20companies%20using%20Copilot%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%20And%20plenty%20of%20Microsoft%20employees%20are%20still%20bullish%20on%20the%20company's%20future%20in%20AI.%20One%20employee%20who%20is%20working%20on%20Copilot%20predicted%20its%20path%20would%20be%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20the%20iPhone%3A%20first%20excitement%20over%20its%20enticing%20novelty%2C%20then%20ambivalence%20about%20its%20value%20to%20daily%20life%2C%20ultimately%20arriving%20at%20ubiquity.%20But%20the%20analogy%2C%20while%20ambitious%2C%20is%20inexact%3A%20Unlike%20Copilot%2C%20the%20iPhone%20could%20do%20everything%20Steve%20Jobs%20said%20it%20could%20do%20when%20it%20debuted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20unlike%20Apple%20under%20Jobs%2C%20Microsoft%20is%20still%20struggling%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20best%20to%20pivot%20its%20considerable%20resources%20to%20serve%20its%20intensive%20focus%20on%20AI.%20Its%20new%20fiscal%20year%20began%20in%20July%2C%20but%20budgets%20for%20several%20teams%20were%20delayed%20by%20months%2C%20according%20to%20an%20employee%20with%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20delay.%20The%20holdup%2C%20the%20person%20said%2C%20is%20atypical%20for%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20usually%20distributes%20budgets%20early%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20the%20internal%20concerns%2C%20those%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20company%20express%20no%20doubt%20about%20going%20all%20in%20on%20artificial%20intelligence.%20They%20caution%20that%20it%20always%20takes%20time%20and%20investment%20to%20develop%20a%20new%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20find%20a%20business%20model%20that%20will%20support%20it.%20Spataro%20said%20Microsoft%20considered%20AI%20as%20important%20as%20the%20invention%20of%20the%20internet%20and%20PCs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20would%20stay%20the%20course%2C%20despite%20the%20massive%20investments%20it%20will%20require.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20have%20that%20strategic%20patience%20%E2%80%94%20no%20matter%20what's%20happening%20%E2%80%94%20to%20just%20focus%20and%20execute%2C%26quot%3B%20Spataro%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20we're%20trying%20to%20do%20as%20a%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fashley-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAshley%20Stewart%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20technology%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%20She%20reports%20on%20enterprise%20technology%20companies%20including%20Microsoft%20and%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%20from%20Seattle.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-artificial-intelligence-bet-doubts-marc-benioff-satya-nadella-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731712013000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6732739a5ec9bfa3d63d5dff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-artificial-intelligence-bet-doubts-marc-benioff-satya-nadella-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Customers%20are%20dissatisfied%20with%20Copilot%2C%20rivals%20are%20circling%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20insiders%20are%20skeptical%3A%20a%20BI%20exclusive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22astewart%40insider.com%20(Ashley%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A106%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busines